The paper deals with data structures for answering distance queries in planar graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory concepts such as cycles and faces, which suggests cs.GT (Graph Theory) as another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions space allocation and query time, which are related to optimization and efficiency, respectively, indicating cs.SI (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which is a common theme in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
